<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn62">  62  This account of the crime or original sin in the park or garden may seem to posit both events, hetero- and homosexual exhibitionism, as occurring at different periods, unlike what is suggested in the I.1 Waterloo episode, and the buggery aspect as graver than that of seduction. The consideration that the second allegation was made by three Welsh Guards reconnects the events. Of interest is the somewhat clearer text of the proto-form in notebook N3 (VI.B.3).153: &lsquo;It is not true that Pop was homosexual / he had been arrested at the request of some nursemaids to whom he had temporarily exposed himself in the Temple gardens.&rsquo;  </div>
